The Federal Government has said it will inaugurate visitation panels to its universities, polytechnics and colleges of education next week. Education Minister Adamu Adamu is expected to perform the inauguration at the National Universities Commission (NUC) office in Abuja between April 12 and 13. The panels to the polytechnics and colleges of education will be inaugurated first, while that of the universities and inter-university centres will follow the next day. The Permanent Secretary in the Federal Ministry of Education, Sonny Echono, announced this in an advertorial.